    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "ArchR also provides functionality to integrate scATAC-seq and scRNA-seq data using Seurat's infrastructure, matching the heterogeneous chromatin accessibility profiles and RNA expression. Single-cell epigenome-to-transcriptome integration is essential for understanding dynamic gene regulatory processes... ArchR performs this cross-data alignment in parallel using slices of the scATAC-seq data.",
      "asbval:note": "The paper explicitly describes ArchR's capability to integrate paired scATAC-seq and scRNA-seq data using Seurat's infrastructure for cross-platform alignment.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41588-021-00790-6",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "How does ArchR ingest paired scRNA-seq gene expression data alongside scATAC-seq chromatin accessibility data and produce a unified reduced-dimension embedding for joint analysis?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:11:26.194448+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Here we present a software suite for single-cell analysis of regulatory chromatin in R (ArchR; https://www.archrproject.com/) that enables fast and comprehensive analysis of single-cell chromatin accessibility data.",
      "asbval:note": "ArchR is the primary tool described throughout the paper for scATAC-seq analysis and integration.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41588-021-00790-6",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "ArchR",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:11:26.194448+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/002",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "This package for single-cell Analysis of Regulatory Chromatin in R (ArchR; https://www.archrproject.com/)",
      "asbval:note": "ArchR is explicitly described as an R package.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41588-021-00790-6",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "yes",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "tools",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "R",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000033"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:11:26.194448+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000338"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/003",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "ArchR performs this cross-data alignment in parallel using slices of the scATAC-seq data (Fig. 4a). When performed on the hematopoiesis dataset, this integration enabled scRNA-seq alignment for >220,000 cells in less than 1 h (Fig. 4b)... The alignment showed high concordance between linked gene expression and inferred gene scores for common hematopoietic marker genes (Fig. 4c and Extended Data Fig. 9a).",
      "asbval:note": "The paper describes integration of scATAC-seq and scRNA-seq data and alignment, but does not explicitly state that a 'joint LSI reduction' or 'combined dimensional embedding' is produced as a single unified object. The integration uses Seurat's infrastructure for alignment and produces linked gene expression and gene scores, but the exact nature of the output object (whether it contains a joint LSI or separate embeddings) is not fully specified in the passages provided.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41588-021-00790-6",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "ArchR project object containing both scATAC-seq and scRNA-seq data with joint LSI reduction and combined dimensional embedding",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:11:26.194448+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_001/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The research question is appropriately scoped to the paper's focus on ArchR's integration capabilities for paired scATAC-seq and scRNA-seq data.",
