    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/005",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To demonstrate trajectory analysis in ArchR on the full hematopoiesis dataset, we again focused on the B cell lineage as an example (Fig. 4d). ArchR traces cells along the B cell differentiation trajectory and identifies 11,999 peak-to-gene links that have correlated regulatory dynamics (r > 0.5) across the B cell differentiation trajectory (Fig. 4e).",
      "asbval:note": "Paper demonstrates trajectory results embedded in ArchR analysis (Fig. 4d shows UMAP with trajectory position), but does not explicitly describe the output as an 'ArchR project object with embedded trajectory result.' The paper shows trajectory analysis produces trajectory positions and linked results, but the specific object structure/format is not detailed in the passages provided.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-s41588-021-00790-6",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_002",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "expected_outputs",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "ArchR project object with embedded trajectory result from selected method",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T18:11:37.386488+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/task_002/scope_drift",
      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The research question focuses on the conditional invocation mechanism (how ArchR dispatches between Monocle3 and Slingshot), which is a technical implementation detail. The paper confirms both methods are implemented but does not provide detailed pseudocode or algorithmic description of the conditional dispatch logic itself.",
        "The card frames this as a task about 'reconstructing' the dispatch mechanism, suggesting reverse-engineering or detailed implementation analysis. The paper documents that both methods are available and benchmarks their performance, but does not provide granular implementation details about the conditional logic."
      ],
      "asbval:n_drift_notes": 2,
